Latvian consumer prices grew at the
slowest pace in 20 months in June as transport costs fell.  The inflation rate dropped to 1.9 percent from 2.2 percent
in May, the  statistics office , based in the capital, Riga, said
today on its website. Prices fell 0.1 percent from the previous
month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
